For the FTP protocol, here are the client request templates using type constraints where appropriate. FTP commands generally consist of a command keyword followed by optional parameters such as file paths, usernames, passwords, or numeric values.

1. USER (specify username)  
```
USER: ["USER <<STRING:1-256>>\r\n"]
```

2. PASS (specify password)  
```
PASS: ["PASS <<STRING:1-256>>\r\n"]
```

3. CWD (change working directory)  
```
CWD: ["CWD <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

4. PWD (print working directory)  
```
PWD: ["PWD\r\n"]
```

5. LIST (list files/directories)  
```
LIST: ["LIST <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```
(Note: The path parameter is optional; if omitted, it lists the current directory.)

6. RETR (retrieve/download a file)  
```
RETR: ["RETR <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

7. STOR (store/upload a file)  
```
STOR: ["STOR <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

8. DELE (delete a file)  
```
DELE: ["DELE <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

9. RNFR (rename from - specify source file)  
```
RNFR: ["RNFR <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

10. RNTO (rename to - specify destination file)  
```
RNTO: ["RNTO <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

11. QUIT (close connection)  
```
QUIT: ["QUIT\r\n"]
```

12. TYPE (set transfer type)  
```
TYPE: ["TYPE <<ENUM:A,I>>\r\n"]
```
(A = ASCII mode, I = Image/binary mode)

13. PORT (specify client data port)  
```
PORT: ["PORT <<INTEGER:0-255>>,<<INTEGER:0-255>>,<<INTEGER:0-255>>,<<INTEGER:0-255>>,<<INTEGER:0-255>>,<<INTEGER:0-255>>\r\n"]
```
(Format: h1,h2,h3,h4,p1,p2 where h1-h4 are IP octets and p1,p2 specify port)

14. PASV (enter passive mode)  
```
PASV: ["PASV\r\n"]
```

15. SYST (get system type)  
```
SYST: ["SYST\r\n"]
```

16. NOOP (no operation)  
```
NOOP: ["NOOP\r\n"]
```

These templates cover the most common FTP client requests with appropriate type constraints. Let me know if you need templates for additional FTP commands.
Here are additional FTP client request templates using type constraints in the specified format:

17. APPE (append to a file)  
```
APPE: ["APPE <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

18. REST (restart transfer at a specific offset)  
```
REST: ["REST <<INTEGER:0-4294967295>>\r\n"]
```
(Note: Offset is a non-negative 32-bit integer)

19. RNFR (rename from - specify source file)  
```
RNFR: ["RNFR <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

20. RNTO (rename to - specify destination file)  
```
RNTO: ["RNTO <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

21. MKD (make directory)  
```
MKD: ["MKD <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

22. RMD (remove directory)  
```
RMD: ["RMD <<PATH>>\r\n"]
```

23. SITE (site-specific commands)  
```
SITE: ["SITE <<STRING:1-512>>\r\n"]
```

24. FEAT (request feature list)  
```
FEAT: ["FEAT\r\n"]
```

25. OPTS (set options for a command)  
```
OPTS: ["OPTS <<STRING:1-256>> <<STRING:1-256>>\r\n"]
```

26. ALLO (allocate storage space)  
```
ALLO: ["ALLO <<INTEGER:0-4294967295>>\r\n"]
```

27. STRU (set file structure)  
```
STRU: ["STRU <<ENUM:F,R,P>>\r\n"]
```
(F = File, R = Record, P = Page)

28. MODE (set transfer mode)  
```
MODE: ["MODE <<ENUM:Z,S,B>>\r\n"]
```
(Z = Compressed, S = Stream, B = Block)

If you need templates for any other FTP commands or further details, feel free to ask!